"date": "1946-06-27", "dates": ["1946-06-27"], "description": ["MARKET SLUMPS SLIGHTLY AFTER PESSIMISTIC DAY Railroads Disappointed by ICC Increase Buyers Strike Talk May Mean 1 roubles lor Labor IVall Nlreid Correspondence Till lepubllciiii New York Juin 25 Sellitit came into the market for industrial stocks thp first hour and continued to the close with the average for this group ending down 102 Evidently holders of railroad stocks are disappointed over the small interim increase just granted by the ICC in freight rates as of July 1 Kails sold off throughout the session ending down 105 which on a percentage basis is a much larger decline than occurred in in1 dust rials id w Southern ra way voiced the opinion of railway exj euuiivea when he declared today that the increase in freight rates is not enough to cover increased overhead that the increase would add 400000 to his companys gross revenue for the last half of this year hut that the recent further advance in rail road wages would add 19000000 to the years operating expenses re serve that the increase in the sell ing price of coal to offset the inj crease in miners wages would add another 2000000 to the years over head When the market"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-04-13T06:26:37.896Z", "group": ["ndnp/mb", "massachusetts-boston-public-library"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83020847/1946-06-27/ed-1/?sp=13", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mb:batch_mb_basil_ver01:data:sn83020847:00517170847:1946062701:0363/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=269&w=200", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mb:batch_mb_basil_ver01:data:sn83020847:00517170847:1946062701:0363/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=539&w=400", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mb:batch_mb_basil_ver01:data:sn83020847:00517170847:1946062701:0363/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1078&w=801", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-se